<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Try the LocalGov IMS Income Management System</h1>

<div class="govuk-panel govuk-panel--confirmation ndx-walkthrough-value-prop">
  <h2 class="govuk-panel__title">
    20 minutes to experience LocalGov IMS
  </h2>
  <div class="govuk-panel__body">
    Process a payment, manage suspense items, run eReturns, and explore council income management.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="govuk-inset-text ndx-walkthrough-reassurance">
  <strong class="govuk-!-font-size-24">No technical knowledge required</strong>
  <p class="govuk-body">
    This walkthrough guides you through <a href="https://localgovims.digital" class="govuk-link">LocalGov IMS</a> as a finance officer would use it.
    You'll process payments, review transactions, manage suspense items, and run end-of-day reports.
    Perfect for finance managers, revenues and benefits staff, and anyone evaluating income management systems.
  </p>
</div>

<p class="govuk-body">
  <a href="https://localgovims.digital" class="govuk-link">LocalGov IMS</a> is an open-source income management system designed for UK local authorities. It handles payment processing, account management, fund allocation, and financial reporting — the core back-office functions that every council needs to manage income from Council Tax, business rates, housing rents, and other revenue streams.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">What you'll do</h2>

<p class="govuk-body-l">
  In this 20-minute walkthrough, you'll:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Process a citizen payment</strong> — Use the payment portal to pay Council Tax through GOV.UK Pay sandbox (5 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Review transactions as a finance officer</strong> — Search accounts, view receipts, and browse transaction history (4 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Handle an unallocated payment</strong> — Find and resolve a suspense item that needs manual allocation (4 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Run end-of-day cashing up</strong> — Generate an eReturn to reconcile the day's transactions (3 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Process a bank file</strong> — Import and review a monthly bank reconciliation file (3 minutes)
  </li>
</ol>

